{{Infobox person | name = Rafael Cañedo Benítez | image = | caption = | birthname = | birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1942|1|1}} | birth_place = [[Puebla, Puebla]], [[Mexico]] | age = | death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|2001|7|10|1942|1|1}} | death_place = | education = | occupation = Businessman and politician | party = {{PRI party}} | alias = | gender = | status = | title = | family = | spouse = | children = | relatives = | nationality = Mexican | religion = | salary = | networth = | credits = | agent = }}
'''Rafael Cañedo Benítez''' (1 January 1942 – 10 July 2001) was a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] businessman and politician affiliated with the [[Institutional Revolutionary Party]]. He served as Senator of the [[LVIII Legislature of the Mexican Congress|LVIII]] and (briefly) the [[LIX Legislature of the Mexican Congress|LIX]] Legislatures of the Mexican Congress representing [[Puebla]] and as Deputy of the LV Legislature.<ref>{{cite web|title=Perfil del legislador|url=http://sil.gobernacion.gob.mx/Librerias/pp_PerfilLegislador.php?SID=&Referencia=2177731|publisher=Legislative Information System|accessdate=15 April 2014}}</ref>
He was the founder of Cinco Radio, a group of radio stations in Puebla.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aniverario Luctuoso de Rafael Cañedo Benítez|url=http://www.cincoradio.com.mx/noticia/aniversario-luctuoso-de-rafael-canedo-benitez|accessdate=15 April 2014|newspaper=Cinco Radio|date=10 July 2012}}</ref>
